⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Cheng Xin
node 3BP · 3BP · ⟦Cheng Xin:3BP:e0abcb⟧

WHO   — Cheng Xin — the Swordholder who couldn't
WHAT  — Mercy as catastrophe: the most humane person in the trilogy, and the reason humanity loses its standoff.
WHERE — 3BP · The Three-Body Problem  Framework inputs: Remembrance of Earth's Past (Liu Cixin, 2014-2016) + the Tencent (2023) & Netflix (2024) series; dual-agent web-verified  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the trilogy's hardest argument is that kindness, in a dark forest, can be a doom — and Cheng Xin embodies it.
HOW   — By accepting the Swordholder's burden, freezing when Trisolaris attacks, and living to witness the dimensional war that follows.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  They handed me the sword because they knew I could not swing it. They were right. I have spent forever asking whether mercy was the sin.

spoken token : vol-zyl-pho   ·   hex : e0abcb
